<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf65b65c1-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3103"><num value="3103">§ 3103.</num><heading> Use of reports, documents, and records</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may rely, as evidence of compliance with this subtitle, on—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf65b65c2-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3103/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> reports, documents, and records of other persons who have been determined by the Secretary to be reliable; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf65b65c3-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3103/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> other methods the Secretary has determined to be reliable.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idf65b65c4-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/104/324/tVI/s603/a">Pub. L. 104–324, title VI, § 603(a)</ref>, <date date="1996-10-19">Oct. 19, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/3930">110 Stat. 3930</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
